CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization, or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during antenna cord sub-assembly removal/installation are shown below.

2. REMOVE NO. 2 HEATER TO REGISTER DUCT SUB-ASSEMBLY

3. REMOVE NO. 2 KNEE PROTECTOR BRACKET

Click here

4. REMOVE NO. 3 KNEE PROTECTOR BRACKET

Click here

5. REMOVE ANTENNA CORD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) for Radio Receiver Type:

(1) Disengage the 6 clamps and remove the antenna cord sub-assembly.

(b) for Navigation Receiver Type:

(1) Disengage the 6 clamps and remove the antenna cord sub-assembly.

6. REMOVE ROOF HEADLINING ASSEMBLY

Click here

7. REMOVE NO. 2 ANTENNA CORD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the adhesive tape from the roof headlining assembly.

*A

w/o Sliding Roof

*B

w/ Sliding Roof

Adhesive Tape

Front

(b) Remove the No. 2 antenna cord sub-assembly from the roof headlining assembly.

8. REMOVE NO. 3 ANTENNA CORD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disconnect the connector.

(b) Disengage the claw.

(c) Disengage the 6 clamps and remove the No. 3 antenna cord sub-assembly.

9. REMOVE BACK DOOR UPPER TRIM PANEL ASSEMBLY

Click here

10. REMOVE BACK DOOR SIDE GARNISH RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

Click here

11. REMOVE NO. 4 ANTENNA CORD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) w/o Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the connector.

(2) Disengage the 2 clamps.

(3) Disconnect the connector.

(b) w/ Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the connector.

(2) Disconnect the washer hose.

HINT:

Use a container to collect the windshield washer fluid.

(3) Disengage the 3 clamps.

(4) Disconnect the connector.

(5) Disconnect the washer hose.

HINT:

Use a container to collect the windshield washer fluid.

(6) Disengage the clamp.

(c) Disengage the 8 claws to separate the 2 grommets.

NOTICE:

When reusing the No. 4 antenna cord sub-assembly, make sure to replace the No. 1 wire harness protector and No. 2 wire harness protector with new ones as reusing them may cause water ingress.

(d) Remove the No. 4 antenna cord sub-assembly.

(e) When reusing the No. 4 antenna cord sub-assembly:

(1) for Back Door Side:

  1. Remove the tape to disconnect the antenna cord from the No. 2 wire harness protector (w/o Rear Wiper).

    Tape

  2. Remove the tape to disconnect the antenna cord and washer hose from the No. 2 wire harness protector (w/ Rear Wiper).

    *a

    Antenna Cord

    *b

    Washer Hose

    Tape

  3. Remove the tape to disconnect the rubber protrusion of the grommet from the No. 2 wire harness protector.

    Tape

(2) Separate the No. 1 wire harness protector from the grommet as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the No. 2 wire harness protector.

(3) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration and remove the No. 1 wire harness protector.

Remove in this Direction

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the No. 2 wire harness protector.
